I'll design a practical business unit onboarding system that captures essential context while remaining manageable. Here's the proposed structure:

## 1. CORE BUSINESS PROFILE (Required Fields)
```json
{
  "basics": {
    "id": "string [slug format]",
    "name": "string",
    "type": "enum [service|product|venue|project]",
    "status": "enum [active|planning|paused]",
    "description": "string [200 char max]"
  },
  "business_model": {
    "revenue_streams": ["string[]"], // Primary ways the business makes money
    "target_market": {
      "primary_audience": "string",
      "price_point": "enum [budget|mid|premium|luxury]",
      "geographic_scope": "enum [local|regional|national|global]"
    },
    "key_offerings": [{
      "name": "string",
      "price_range": {
        "min": "number",
        "max": "number",
        "unit": "enum [flat|hourly|monthly]"
      },
      "description": "string [100 char max]"
    }]
  },
  "metrics": {
    "current_revenue": {
      "amount": "number",
      "frequency": "enum [monthly|annual]"
    },
    "target_revenue": {
      "amount": "number", 
      "timeframe": "string"
    }
  }
}
```

## 2. ENHANCED CONTEXT (Optional Fields)
```json
{
  "market_position": {
    "competitors": ["string[]"],
    "differentiators": ["string[]"],
    "industry_trends": ["string[]"]
  },
  "operations": {
    "team_size": "number",
    "key_tools": ["string[]"],
    "processes": ["string[]"]
  },
  "assets": {
    "website": "url",
    "social_profiles": [{
      "platform": "string",
      "url": "string"
    }],
    "brand_assets": "url" // Link to brand kit
  }
}
```

## 3. DATA VALIDATION RULES
- All required fields must be non-empty
- IDs must be URL-safe slugs
- Prices must be positive numbers
- URLs must be valid
- Enums must match defined options
- Arrays must have at least one item
- Text fields have specified character limits

## 4. MAPPING TO EXISTING STRUCTURES

```javascript
// portfolio.json mapping
{
  "id": "basics.id",
  "name": "basics.name", 
  "type": "basics.type",
  "status": "basics.status"
}

// config.json mapping
{
  "business": {
    "model": "business_model",
    "metrics": "metrics"
  },
  "market": "market_position",
  "operations": "operations"
}

// gst.json mapping
{
  "goals": {
    "revenue": "metrics.target_revenue",
    "market": "target_market"
  }
}

// brand.json mapping
{
  "assets": "assets",
  "voice": {
    "market_position": "market_position.differentiators"
  }
}
```

## 5. INTAKE WORKFLOW

1. Initial Setup (Business Owner/Manager)
- Complete Core Business Profile
- Provide basic metrics and targets
- Define key offerings and pricing

2. Strategic Review (SuperChase Team)
- Validate data completeness
- Add market research insights
- Map to GST framework
- Request any missing critical context

3. Technical Setup (SuperChase Dev)
- Generate config files
- Set up monitoring
- Enable relevant integrations
- Validate data structure

4. Ongoing Maintenance
- Quarterly metric updates
- Annual strategic review
- On-demand updates for major changes

## Implementation Notes:

1. Build as a multi-step form interface with:
- Progress tracking
- Save drafts
- Validation feedback
- Help text/examples

2. Create import/export tools for:
- Spreadsheet bulk import
- API integration
- Config file generation

3. Include templates for common business types:
- Service business preset
- Product brand preset
- Venue preset
- Project preset

This framework provides enough context for agents to work with real data while remaining practical to implement and maintain. The modular structure allows for future expansion while maintaining compatibility with existing SuperChase systems.
